      <section eId="sec_33_2_20">
        <num>33-2-20</num>
        <content>
          <p>If any person is entitled to a hearing by any provision of this title before any proposed action is taken, the notice of the proposed action may be in the form of a notice to show cause stating that the proposed action may be taken, unless such person shows cause at a hearing to be held as specified in the notice why the proposed action should not be taken and stating the basis of the proposed action.</p>
          <p>(Code 1933, ยง 56-221, enacted by Ga. L. 1960, p. 289, ยง 1.)</p>
